HEADWORD: Goolde
<hw>Goolde</hw> <pr>(g⟦oomac⟧ld)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An old English name of some yellow flower, -- the
marigold (<gen>Calendula</gen>), according to <person>Dr.
Prior</person>, but in Chaucer perhaps the turnsole.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

